cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.SY, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses fault-tolerance techniques for Massively Parallel Stream Processing Engines (MPSPE), which are typically implemented in a distributed and parallel computing environment. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes algorithms to optimize a partially active replication plan. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is another possible category as stream processing engines are often used for real-time data processing and analysis, which is a common use case for databases. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses a fault-tolerance framework for a complex system (MPSPE) and proposes algorithms to optimize its performance. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed fault-tolerance framework on top of an open-source stream processing engine (Storm).
